N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 8 ยง 3.13 - Committee on geographic names

State Regulations
(a) The commissioner with the approval of the

Regents shall appoint a committee on geographic names of five members. The
committee shall determine, subject to approval by the Regents, place names in

New York State pursuant to section
174
of the

Education Law. (b) The committee
shall submit its findings to the Regents for final action. Notes
